+ 1 CLIP
1/1 WHAT NEXT?    <CLIP BEFORE>  or  <CLIP AFTER>
 
 
 
CLIP is a way of mass deleting whole chunks of text.
 
You can either CLIP everything BEFORE the "Top Line of the Screen"
or AFTER.
+ 2 CREATE
1/1 WHAT NEXT?   <CREATE>
 
 
 
CREATE allows you to open a new T/Maker File.   T/Maker asks:
 
1/1 WHAT FILE NAME?
 
All files names must be unique.
 
 
Anything contained in  T/Maker's  work space will be REPLACED
by issuing the CREATE command. That means if you want to SAVE
whatever work is in  the  work space,   make sure  you  do  a
SAVE before CREATE-ing a new file.
+ 2 DATA
1/1 WHAT NEXT?   <DATA>
 
 
 
DATA specifies a new, temporary disk drive to GET and SAVE files from.
 
 
T/Maker will look for files from the  DATA  drive for the  entire work
session unless you request a new DATA drive.
 
 
You can change the "default" DATA drive.  See  Reference Manual  under
"Customization Notes" for details.
+ 2 DELETE
1/1 WHAT NEXT?   <DELETE>   erases a file from a disk.
+ 2 DO
 
1/1 WHAT NEXT?    <DO>
 
 
 
DO   will take the line on the  " Top  of the Screen ",  drop it to
the WHAT NEXT?  prompt line, and execute any commands on this line.
+ 2 FILES
1/1 WHAT NEXT?   <FILES>
 
 
 
FILES will show you a listing of files on the specified drive.
+ 2 GET
1/1 WHAT NEXT?   <GET>  or  <G>
 
 
 
GET will "get" a Disk File  (a file that has been  SAVEd on
disk)  and bring it into T/Maker's work space.
 
 
Anything contained in T/Maker's work space will be REPLACED
by issuing the GET command.  That means if you want to SAVE
whatever work is in the work space, make sure you do a SAVE
before GET-ting a new file to EDIT.
