+ 1 PROOF
1/1 WHAT NEXT?   <PROOF>
 
The  PROOF  command checks the active area for any words that are not in the
standard T/Maker dictionary.
 
PROOF prepares a double column "correction list" of unknown words like this:
 
=!  comming  comming
 
Think of the first occurrence of the word as the current spelling.
Think of the second occurrence as the corrected spelling (you must use the
Editor to correct it).
 
PROOF also marks unindentified words in the text with [  ?=  ].
An example of how this looks is ?=comming.
+ 2 CORRECT
1/1 WHAT NEXT?   <CORRECT>
 
 
CORRECT  will  "correct"  spellings based on the "correction list".  You
must EDIT this list to enter the correct spellings before using CORRECT.
 
 
...........AFTER PROOF.........................AFTER EDITING............
=! compny        compny            |    =! compny         company
=! Ferrari       Ferrari           |    =! Ferrari        Ferrari
...................................|....................................
 
"compny"  - obvious misspelling, correct the second occurrence of  word.
"Ferrari" - the spelling is correct, leave the line alone.
 
A use of CORRECT would correct misspellings, delete the correction lines
and remove "?=" markers from the text.
 
See documentation for other options of correct.
+ 2 SPELL
1/1 WHAT NEXT?  <SPELL word>  or  <SPELL IT>
 
 
SPELL lists words from Dictionary on screen or places them on Correction Lines.
 
You must give SPELL an Ambiguous Word Reference made up of letters and:
 
    ?   question marks to represent one unknown letter.
    *   asterisks used to represent zero or more unknown letters.
 
...............................................................................
                                  This command would list all words that start
1/1 WHAT NEXT?   <SPELL spe*ing>  with " SPE " and end  with " ING ".
 
 
                                  This  command  would add words to correction
1/1 WHAT NEXT?   <SPELL IT>       lines containing ambiguous words.    Result:
 
                          =!  compatable  compat*   compatibility  compatible
+ 2 AMEND
